insisted%20that%20his%20company%20remain%20at%20Hot%20Springs%2C%20the%20task%20befell%20the%20Alphas.%20And%20that%20is%20how%2C%20in%20October%2C%20about%2060%20soldiers%20arrived%20at%20the%20Galwan%20post%3A%20unexpectedly%20and%20without%20much%20preparation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-olk-copy-source%3D%5C%22MessageBody%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENumerous%20difficulties%20would%20beset%20the%20Alphas%20at%20Galwan.%20Apart%20from%20heavy%20snowfall%2C%20Chinese%20posts%20closed%20off%20the%20land%20route%20completely.%20The%20post%20was%20entirely%20dependent%20on%20air%20supplies%2C%20which%20meant%20that%20on%20occasion%2C%20supplies%20would%20also%20land%20on%20the%20enemy%20side.%20The%20Chinese%20also%20kept%20up%20their%20attacks%20to%20demoralise%20the%20Alphas%20by%20circling%20the%20posts%20and%20yelling%20propaganda%20slogans%20like%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Hindi%20Chini%20Bhai%20Bhai'.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Jats%20prepared%20four%20posts%20in%20the%20complex%3A%20the%20company%20headquarters%20with%20one%20section%20under%20Major%20Srikant%20Sitaram%20Hasabnis%2C%20a%20platoon%20under%20Subedar%20Hoshiar%20Singh%2C%20another%20section%20under%20Naik%20Inder%20Singh%2C%20and%20a%20post%20comprising%20the%20remaining%20men%20under%20Subedar%20Nihal%20Singh.%20There%20was%20no%20communication%20between%20these%20posts.%20Supplies%20were%20in%20limited%20numbers%20too%2C%20with%2016%20soldiers%20reportedly%20lacking%20any%20kind%20of%20weaponry.%20Even%20the%20radio%20communication%20between%20the%20headquarters%20of%20the%20company%20and%20that%20of%20the%20battalion%20was%20only%20as%20per%20schedule.%20Every%20soldier%20was%20scared%20and%20felt%20as%20though%20they%20had%20been%20thrown%20into%20a%20death%20trap.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20Bullets%20Rained%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EA%20week%20passed%20eventlessly%20after%20the%20last%20soldier%20landed%20in%20Galwan.%20But%20it%20was%20an%20eerie%20peace%2C%20not%20to%20last%20too%20long.%20In%20the%20early%20hours%20of%20October%2020%2C%20Major%20Hasabnis%2C%20who%20was%20in%20his%20tent%20then%2C%20heard%20a%20machine%20gun%20being%20fired%20at%20his%20post.%20As%20he%20peeked%20outside%2C%20he%20was%20met%20with%20a%20barrage%20of%20firing%20from%20the%20Chinese%20side.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20no%20time%2C%20firing%20from%20all%20directions%20engulfed%20the%20area.%20Bullets%20from%20rifles%2C%20machine%20guns%2C%20and%20artillery%20were%20pelting%20the%20ground.%20Major%20Hasabnis%20approached%20the%20tent%20with%20the%20radio%20to%20alert%20the%20battalion%20and%20brigade%20headquarters%20that%20they%20had%20been%20attacked%20by%20the%20Chinese.%20Except%2C%20it%20was%20radio%20silence%20period%20at%20the%20headquarters%2C%20which%20meant%20that%20there%20was%20no%20one%20to%20alert%20or%20ask%20for%20help%20from.%20The%20Alphas%2C%20thus%2C%20with%20no%20contact%20with%20the%20outside%20world%2C%20were%20now%20left%20to%20tackle%20the%20Chinese%20all%20by%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20remaining%20company%20positions%20were%20out%20of%20sight.%20Amid%20heavy%20gunfire%2C%20a%20company%20headquarters%20soldier%20was%20seen%20sitting%20outside%2C%20in%20the%20open.%20Someone%20questioned%20him%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20are%20you%20doing%20this%3F%26quot%3B%20He%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EIntezaar%2C%20Saab%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3BWaiting%2C%20Sir%26quot%3B).%20One%20of%20the%2016%20unarmed%20men%2C%20he%20was%20waiting%20for%20the%20shot%20that%20would%20kill%20him.%20Even%20Major%20Hasabnis%20had%20but%20just%20a%20pistol%20on%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeterred%20By%20Nothing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESubedar%20Nihal%20Singh's%20post%20was%20also%20pounded.%20After%20the%20shelling%20stopped%20for%20a%20while%2C%20the%20infantry%20launched%20a%20battalion-sized%20assault%20on%20the%20forward%20defences.%20Troops%20kept%20fighting%20from%20their%20crumbling%20defences%2C%20and%20amidst%20that%2C%20Nihal%20Singh%20went%20from%20man%20to%20man%2C%20encouraging%20them%20to%20fight%20till%20the%20end.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENot%20too%20far%20away%2C%20the%20JCO%20was%20fatally%20wounded%20in%20shelling.%20Upon%20noticing%20this%2C%20Sepoy%20Bhopal%20Singh%20immediately%20ran%20to%20him%2C%20gave%20him%20aid%2C%20and%20moved%20him%20to%20a%20safe%20location.%20He%20found%20his%20LMG-1%20severely%20wounded%20when%20he%20returned%20to%20his%20trench.%20Even%20so%2C%20he%20took%20control%20of%20the%20weapon%20and%20dealt%20severe%20casualties%20to%20the%20enemy.%20Ultimately%2C%20when%20he%20was%20left%20with%20only%20grenades%2C%20he%20lobbed%20them%20at%20the%20enemy%20defiantly%2C%20causing%20numerous%20fatalities.%20Eventually%2C%20however%2C%20as%20the%20front-line%20defences%20crumbled%20completely%2C%20Bhopal%20Singh%20was%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFighting%20Till%20The%20End%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Major%20Hasabnis%2C%20in%20the%20rear%20position%2C%20continued%20to%20take%20on%20the%20Chinese%20with%20his%20remaining%20troops.%20Captain%20Doctor%20HN%20Paul%20was%20advised%20to%20exit%20the%20tent%20and%20enter%20the%20trench.%20But%20before%20he%20could%20do%20so%2C%20the%20tent%20caught%20fire%20due%20to%20an%20incendiary%20round%3B%20he%20was%20presumed%20to%20have%20died.%20Company%20Havildar%20Major%20Banwari%20Lal%2C%20who%20was%20charged%20with%20organising%20ammunition%2C%20was%20also%20killed%20by%20a%20shell%20when%20he%20was%20sprinting%20to%20supply%20ammo.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Left%2C%20Major%20S.S.%20Hasabnis%2C%20and%20right%2C%20Subedar%20Nihal%20Singh%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Left%2C%20Major%20S.S.%20Hasabnis%2C%20and%20right%2C%20Subedar%20Nihal%20Singh%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fu207i6k8_hasabnis_625x300_11_November_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeft%2C%20Major%20S.S.%20Hasabnis%2C%20and%20right%2C%20Subedar%20Nihal%20Singh%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESubedar%20Hoshiar%20Singh's%20isolated%20location%20wasn't%20spared%20either.%20Although%20the%20initial%20wave%20of%20the%20attack%20was%20repelled%2C%20the%20sheer%20extent%20of%20it%20was%20overwhelming.%20It%20was%20clear%20to%20Singh%20that%20it%20was%20a%20dire%20moment.%20After%20his%20LMG%20operators%20sustained%20fatal%20injuries%2C%20he%20personally%20fired%20the%20weapon%20and%20took%20on%20the%20adversary%2C%20before%20being%20shot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENaik%20Inder%20Singh's%20weak%20section%20also%20took%20on%20a%20four%20times%20larger%20enemy%20valiantly.%20The%20section%20gave%20it%20all%20it%20had%2C%20but%20after%20an%20hour%2C%20when%20they%20had%20nothing%20left%2C%20they%20fell%2C%20with%20the%20enemy%20taking%20on%20their%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20The%20Chinese%20Seized%20The%20Post%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20hail%20of%20gunfire%20ended%20quickly%2C%20just%20as%20it%20had%20begun.%20Unsettling%20silence%20suddenly%20descended%20over%20the%20Galwan%20complex.%20Hand-to-hand%20combat%20broke%20out%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20adversary%20closed.%20Soldiers%20who%20were%20hurt%20could%20be%20heard%20screaming.%20After%20several%20hours%20of%20fighting%2C%20the%20Chinese%20took%20complete%20control%20of%20the%20post%2C%20killing%2030%20Indian%20soldiers%2C%20including%20Dr.%20Paul.%20Eighteen%20men%20suffered%20serious%20injuries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20men%20fought%20until%20the%20last%20bullet%20was%20shot.%20And%20even%20though%20they%20knew%20death%20and%20defeat%20were%20staring%20them%20in%20the%20eye%2C%20they%20did%20not%20raise%20the%20white%20flag%20of%20surrender.%20Major%20Hasabnis%20and%20his%20surviving%20soldiers%20were%20taken%20prisoner%20by%20the%20enemy.%20Galwan%20had%20been%20seized.%20Subedar%20Nihal%20Singh%20and%20one%20OR%20died%20in%20captivity%2C%20while%20Sepoy%20Roshan%20Lal%20lost%20his%20limbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20picture%20of%205%20Jat%20when%20it%20reached%20Chushul%20to%20relieve%201%2F8%20Gorkha%20Rifles%20from%20several%20forward%20posts.%20%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22A%20picture%20of%205%20Jat%20when%20it%20reached%20Chushul%20to%20relieve%201%2F8%20Gorkha%20Rifles%20from%20several%20forward%20posts.%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2F9kutdgto_jats_625x300_11_November_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20picture%20of%205%20Jat%20when%20it%20reached%20Chushul%20to%20relieve%201%2F8%20Gorkha%20Rifles%20from%20several%20forward%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOn%20October%2021%2C%20Chinese%20soldiers%20again%20opened%20fire%20on%20Indian%20helicopters%20as%20they%20flew%20over%20the%20Galwan%20position.%20The%20pilot%2C%20after%20seeing%20no%20sign%20of%20life%20at%20the%20post%2C%20concluded%20that%20every%20single%20man%20had%20either%20been%20killed%20or%20taken%20prisoner.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIt%20was%20only%20in%20May%201963%20that%20the%20captives%20were%20finally%20repatriated.%20Among%20them%2C%20Subedar%20Nihal%20Singh%20was%20posthumously%20awarded%20Vir%20Chakra%20in%20recognition%20of%20his%20bravery%20and%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E(All%20photos%20courtesy%20of%20the%20author)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E(Jai%20Samota%20is%20a%20student%20and%20writer%20from%20Barisadri%2C%20Chittorgarh%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20and%20author%20of%20'Major%20Shaitan%20Singh%2C%20PVC%3A%20The%20Man%20in%20Ha